oomtopia.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/tarahm-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>\r\nLearn Bharathanatyam, an ancient Classical dance form originating in Tamil Nadu (India) over 2000 years ago.\r\nDiscover the beauty of athletic grace and the intricacy of story-telling through hand-gestures.\r\nChallenge yourself to discover the dancer within.\r\n\r\n<strong>ALL LEVELS:-\r\n<em>Drop-in! </em></strong>These classes are designed to help you understand the basic tools of Bharathanatyam.\r\n<em><strong>Join the 10-week intro series.</strong></em> This progressive series teaches you a more extensive Bharathanatyam vocabulary, pure dance sequences, and story-telling elements that can perhaps awaken the performer in you.\r\n\r\n<strong>Drop-in Classes:-\r\n</strong>Wednesday - 6:00-7:00pm\r\nThursday - 10am - 11am\r\nSaturday - 11am - 12 noon\r\nCost: Single class - $15; Monthly (one class per week) - $50; Monthly (unlimited classes) - $80.\r\n\r\n<strong>10-Week Series:</strong>\r\nStarts April 10th, Saturday, 10am - 11am\r\n$130 for entire series. Email<a href=\"mailto:Subashinig@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"mailto:Subashinig@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">Subashinig@gmail.com</a> to register and get details.\r\n\r\n<strong>Location: </strong>at Zoomtopia, 810 SE Belmont, Suite 6 (two blks from Oregon Ballet Theatre)\r\n\r\n<strong>Contact: </strong>Subashini Ganesan (Founder, Choreographer, Teacher);<a href=\"http://www.natyaleela.com\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"http://www.natyaleela.com\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.natyaleela.com</a>; 503-449-6160;<a href=\"mailto:subashinig@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"mailto:subashinig@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">subashinig@gmail.com</a>\r\n\r\nLooking forward to seeing many of you on the dance floor!\r\nSuba\r\n--\r\nSubashini Ganesan\r\nFounder, Choreographer, Teacher - Natya Leela Academy\r\nResident Artist - Young Audiences Oregon\r\n810 SE Belmont, Suite 6\r\nPortland, OR 97214\r\n503-449-6160;<span style=\"font-size: 13.3333px;\"><a href=\"http://www.natyaleela.com\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.natyaleela.com</a></span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://zoomtopia.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/nwfolk1.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-339\" title=\"nwfolk1\" src=\"http://zoomtopia.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/nwfolk1-300x216.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"216\" /></a>','Zoomtopia Welcomes our Newest Member, Natya Leela Academy',0,'','publish','open','open','','zoomtopia-welcomes-our-newest-member-natya-leela-academy','','','2010-04-06 16:54:37','2010-04-06 23:54:37','',0,'http://zoomtopia.com/?p=337',0,'post','',0),(411,1,'2013-11-04 17:35:44','2013-11-05 00:35:44','','Zoomtopia Dance Studio, Studio #2',0,'','inherit','open','open','','zoomtopia-dance-studio-studio-2-2','','','2013-11-04 17:35:44','2013-11-05 00:35:44','',0,'http://zoomtopia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Zoomtopia-7.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(123,2,'2009-05-12 00:59:22','2009-05-12 07:59:22','ZoomTopia is a new creative space at 810 SE Belmont in the vibrant inner SE industrial district inPortland, Oregon. This project is intended to offer artists, dancers, creatives and nonprofits the chance to participate in an affordable, communal building that they will have the option to buy in the near term. The building is currently undergoing renovation and will be ready for occupancy in late summer/early fall. We have pre-leased about half the building and are seeking new tenants who will benefit from the concept and contribute to the community we are building. Interested parties should contact Carole Zoom: carole@zoomtopia.com or 541.954.8373','Philosophy',0,'','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-8','','','2009-05-12 00:59:22','2009-05-12 07:59:22','',2,'http://zoomtopia.com/2-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(122,2,'2009-04-26 12:15:46','2009-04-26 19:15:46','Zoomtopia is a new creative space at 810 SE Belmont in Portland, Oregon. The 